ages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand what GitHub Copilot CLI looks like from the outside to plan e2e testing:\\n\\n1. Search the codebase for any references to the copilot CLI binary name (e.g., \\\"copilot\\\", \\\"gh copilot\\\", \\\"github-copilot\\\") — how is it invoked?\\n2. Look at the copilot agent's `FormatResumeCommand` to understand the CLI command\\n3. Look at how claude-code e2e tests launch the agent — search for exec.Command, os/exec usage in e2e tests\\n4. Check if there's any agent launcher abstraction or if each agent needs its own launcher\\n5. Search for any existing copilot-related test utilities or mocks\\n6. Look at the `setup.go` or `setup_test.go` files for how agents are detected/launched\\n\\nFocus on understanding the practical requirements: what binary needs to be installed, what commands are run, how stdin/stdout work.\",\"agentId\":\"addc259\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012PWda36dSmV5zirzjWtqNd\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_0181CEqf7GRSQXhM1YhRyiu9\",\"uuid\":\"bdfff0fe-f668-419c-88e6-03fdfdaa046c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:25:01.690Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"bdfff0fe-f668-419c-88e6-03fdfdaa046c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d98d9846-735d-41ce-925a-44f40eb856a8\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/github-copilot-support\",\"slug\":\"rustling-beaming-porcupine\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01KcQJ2Kjb4qe6TW5gFJwtpV\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Plan: GitHub Copilot CLI Agent Integration\\n     2→\\n     3→## Context\\n     4→\\n     5→The Entire CLI currently integrates with Claude Code (stable) and Gemini CLI (preview) via a generic Agent interface. GitHub Copilot CLI is a standalone terminal agent (`copilot` command) that supports hooks similar to Claude/Gemini. This plan adds Copilot as a third agent integration (preview status).\\n     6→\\n     7→**Good news**: All Copilot hooks include common fields `sessionId`, `transcript_path`, and `hookEventName` in their stdin JSON. Additionally, `agentStop` provides TurnEnd support. This means the integration follows the same pattern as Claude/Gemini.\\n     8→\\n     9→---\\n    10→\\n    11→## Hook Inventory (8 hooks)\\n    12→\\n    13→| Copilot Hook | CLI Subcommand | Normalized Event | Notes |\\n    14→|---|---|---|---|\\n    15→| `sessionStart` | `session-start` | `SessionStart` | Session begins or resumes |\\n    16→| `sessionEnd` | `session-end` | `SessionEnd` | Session completes/terminated |\\n    17→| `userPromptSubmitted` | `user-prompt-submitted` | `TurnStart` | User submits prompt |\\n    18→| `agentStop` | `agent-stop` | `TurnEnd` | Agent finished responding |\\n    19→| `subagentStop` | `subagent-stop` | `SubagentEnd` | Subagent completed |\\n    20→| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil` | Pass-through |\\n    21→| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil` | Pass-through |\\n    22→| `errorOccurred` | `error-occurred` | `nil` | Logging only |\\n    23→\\n    24→**Common stdin fields** (all hooks): `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `hookEventName`, `transcript_path`\\n    25→\\n    26→**Hook-specific fields**: `source`/`initialPrompt` (sessionStart), `reason` (sessionEnd), `prompt` (userPromptSubmitted), `toolName`/`toolArgs` (preToolUse/postToolUse), `toolResult` (postToolUse), `error` (errorOccurred)\\n    27→\\n    28→---\\n    29→\\n    30→## Step 0: Verify Hook stdin Format\\n    31→\\n    32→**Before writing code**, capture actual stdin JSON to confirm the common fields and `agentStop`/`subagentStop` format:\\n    33→\\n    34→```json\\n    35→{\\n    36→  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n    37→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    38→    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"bash\\\": \\\"cat > /tmp/copilot-session-start.json\\\", \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10}],\\n    39→    \\\"agentStop\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"bash\\\": \\\"cat > /tmp/copilot-agent-stop.json\\\", \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10}],\\n    40→    \\\"userPromptSubmitted\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"bash\\\": \\\"cat > /tmp/copilot-user-prompt.json\\\", \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10}]\\n    41→  }\\n    42→}\\n    43→```\\n    44→\\n    45→Place at `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json`, run `copilot`, check `/tmp/copilot-*.json`. Confirm `sessionId` and `transcript_path` are present.\\n    46→\\n    47→---\\n    48→\\n    49→## Step 1: Add Registry Constants\\n    50→\\n    51→**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`\\n    52→\\n    53→```go\\n    54→// In AgentName constants:\\n    55→AgentNameCopilot AgentName = \\\"github-copilot\\\"\\n    56→\\n    57→// In AgentType constants:\\n    58→AgentTypeCopilot AgentType = \\\"GitHub Copilot\\\"\\n    59→```\\n    60→\\n    61→---\\n    62→\\n    63→## Step 2: Create `cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/types.go`\\n    64→\\n    65→Follow `geminicli/types.go` pattern. Copilot uses camelCase JSON fields.\\n    66→\\n    67→**Hook config types:**\\n    68→```go\\n    69→type CopilotHookConfig struct {\\n    70→    Version int                           `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n    71→    Hooks   map[string][]CopilotHookEntry `json:\\\"hooks\\\"`\\n    72→}\\n    73→\\n    74→type CopilotHookEntry struct {\\n    75→    Type       string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    76→    Bash       string `json:\\\"bash\\\"`\\n    77→    TimeoutSec int    `json:\\\"timeoutSec,omitempty\\\"`\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→**Common stdin base (embedded in all hook input structs):**\\n    82→```go\\n    83→type hookBase struct {\\n    84→    SessionID      string `json:\\\"sessionId\\\"`\\n    85→    TranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n    86→    Cwd            string `json:\\\"cwd\\\"`\\n    87→    HookEventName  string `json:\\\"hookEventName\\\"`\\n    88→    Timestamp      string `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n    89→}\\n    90→```\\n    91→\\n    92→**Hook-specific stdin types:**\\n    93→- `sessionStartRaw` - embeds `hookBase` + `Source string`, `InitialPrompt string`\\n    94→- `sessionEndRaw` - embeds `hookBase` + `Reason string`\\n    95→- `userPromptRaw` - embeds `hookBase` + `Prompt string`\\n    96→- `agentStopRaw` - embeds `hookBase` (no extra fields expected)\\n    97→- `subagentStopRaw` - embeds `hookBase` (+ possibly subagent metadata)\\n    98→- `toolUseRaw` - embeds `hookBase` + `ToolName string`, `ToolArgs json.RawMessage`, `ToolResult json.RawMessage`\\n    99→- `errorRaw` - embeds `hookBase` + `Error json.RawMessage`\\n   100→\\n   101→**Tool name constants:**\\n   102→```go\\n   103→const (\\n   104→    ToolEdit   = \\\"edit\\\"\\n   105→    ToolCreate = \\\"create\\\"\\n   106→)\\n   107→var FileModificationTools = []string{ToolEdit, ToolCreate}\\n   108→```\\n   109→\\n   110→---\\n   111→\\n   112→## Step 3: Create `cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/copilot.go`\\n   113→\\n   114→Core agent. Follow `geminicli/gemini.go` as template.\\n   115→\\n   116→**Self-registration:**\\n   117→```go\\n   118→func init() {\\n   119→    agent.Register(agent.AgentNameCopilot, NewCopilotAgent)\\n   120→}\\n   121→```\\n   122→\\n   123→**Identity:**\\n   124→- `Name()` → `agent.AgentNameCopilot`\\n   125→- `Type()` → `agent.AgentTypeCopilot`\\n   126→- `Description()` → `\\\"GitHub Copilot - GitHub's AI coding assistant\\\"`\\n   127→- `IsPreview()` → `true`\\n   128→- `ProtectedDirs()` → `[]string{}` (`.github` is shared, not ours)\\n   129→\\n   130→**Detection** (`DetectPresence()`):\\n   131→- Check for `.github/hooks/` with an Entire copilot hook file present (AreHooksInstalled)\\n   132→- OR check `~/.copilot/` directory existence\\n   133→- Use `paths.RepoRoot()` for repo-relative checks\\n   134→\\n   135→**Session storage:**\\n   136→- `GetHookConfigPath()` → `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json`\\n   137→- `GetSessionDir(repoPath)` → `~/.copilot/session-state/` (with `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` override)\\n   138→- `ResolveSessionFile(dir, sessionID)` → `filepath.Join(dir, sessionID, \\\"events.jsonl\\\")`\\n   139→- `FormatResumeCommand(sessionID)` → `copilot --resume`\\n   140→\\n   141→**Transcript storage** (JSONL - reuse existing helpers):\\n   142→- `ReadTranscript(sessionRef)` → `os.ReadFile(sessionRef)`\\n   143→- `ChunkTranscript(content, maxSize)` → `agent.ChunkJSONL(content, maxSize)`\\n   144→- `ReassembleTranscript(chunks)` → `agent.ReassembleJSONL(chunks)`\\n   145→\\n   146→**Legacy methods:** ParseHookInput, GetSessionID, ReadSession, WriteSession (follow Gemini pattern)\\n   147→\\n   148→---\\n   149→\\n   150→## Step 4: Create `cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/lifecycle.go`\\n   151→\\n   152→Event parsing. Follow `geminicli/lifecycle.go` pattern.\\n   153→\\n   154→**Compile-time assertions:**\\n   155→```go\\n   156→var _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*CopilotAgent)(nil)\\n   157→```\\n   158→\\n   159→**`ParseHookEvent` switch:**\\n   160→```go\\n   161→case HookNameSessionStart  → parseSessionStart(stdin)  → agent.SessionStart\\n   162→case HookNameUserPromptSubmitted → parseTurnStart(stdin) → agent.TurnStart (with Prompt)\\n   163→case HookNameAgentStop     → parseTurnEnd(stdin)        → agent.TurnEnd\\n   164→case HookNameSessionEnd    → parseSessionEnd(stdin)     → agent.SessionEnd\\n   165→case HookNameSubagentStop  → parseSubagentEnd(stdin)    → agent.SubagentEnd\\n   166→case HookNamePreToolUse, HookNamePostToolUse, HookNameErrorOccurred → nil\\n   167→```\\n   168→\\n   169→**Internal parse functions** (use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]` generic helper):\\n   170→- `parseSessionStart` → reads `sessionStartRaw`, returns Event{SessionStart, SessionID, SessionRef}\\n   171→- `parseTurnStart` → reads `userPromptRaw`, returns Event{TurnStart, SessionID, SessionRef, Prompt}\\n   172→- `parseTurnEnd` → reads `agentStopRaw`, returns Event{TurnEnd, SessionID, SessionRef}\\n   173→- `parseSessionEnd` → reads `sessionE