ns first agent whose DetectPresence() returns true\\n    // Used when no explicit agent is specified\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**E2E Test Agent Import** (`cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go:5-8`):\\n```go\\nimport _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"\\nimport _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli\\\"\\nimport _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot\\\"\\n```\\n\\nAgents are imported via blank imports to trigger their `init()` functions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. E2E Test Infrastructure Details\\n\\n**Binary Building** (`setup_test.go:32-52`):\\n- Built once in TestMain before any tests run\\n- Placed in temp directory with unique path per test run\\n- Added to PATH so hooks can find it via `entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg`, etc.\\n- Shared across all tests to avoid repeated builds\\n\\n**Test Environment Isolation** (`testenv.go:47-65`):\\n- Each test gets its own temporary git repository\\n- Symlinks resolved on macOS (for `/var` → `/private/var`)\\n- Git configured with test user credentials\\n- GPG signing disabled for test commits\\n\\n**Hook Execution** (`testenv.go:261-329` - `GitCommitWithShadowHooks`):\\n1. Stage files with go-git\\n2. Write commit message to `.git/COMMIT_EDITMSG`\\n3. Invoke: `entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg <file> message`\\n4. Read modified message (with Entire-Checkpoint trailer added)\\n5. Create commit with go-git\\n6. Invoke: `entire hooks git post-commit`\\n\\nBoth hooks are called via direct `exec.Command` with test env vars set.\\n\\n**Environment Variables for Hooks** (`testenv.go:280-284`):\\n```go\\nprepCmd.Env = append(os.Environ(),\\n    \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1\\\",\\n    \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR=\\\"+filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".claude\\\"),\\n    \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR=\\\"+filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \\\".gemini\\\"),\\n)\\n```\\n\\nThese allow hooks to find agent project directories in test repos.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 8. Test Scenario Coverage\\n\\n