xists(t, env)` - Verify checkpoint trailer in history\\n- `AssertBranchExists(t, env, branchName)` - Branch existence\\n- `AssertAgentSuccess(t, result, err)` - Agent exit code check\\n- `AssertExpectedFilesExist(t, env, prompt)` - Files from prompt template\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 10. Key Architectural Patterns\\n\\n**1. Multi-Agent Support:**\\n- AgentRunner interface allows any agent to be tested\\n- E2E_AGENT env var selects which agent to test\\n- Each agent has its own Runner implementation\\n- Tests auto-skip if agent unavailable\\n\\n**2. Hook Simulation:**\\n- Hooks are NOT simulated - they're actual CLI invocations\\n- Tests manually call `entire hooks git <hook>` like real git would\\n- This tests the actual hook implementation, not a mock\\n\\n**3. Real Agent Invocation:**\\n- Tests invoke the actual agent CLI (e.g., `claude` command)\\n- No agent mocking or stubbing\\n- Requires agent to be installed and authenticated\\n- Timeout handling prevents hanging tests\\n\\n**4. Checkpoint Validation:**\\n- `ValidateCheckpoint()` helper performs comprehensive validation\\n- Checks metadata branch structure (`entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n- Verifies sharded directory format: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`\\n- Validates JSONL transcript format\\n- Checks content hashes match\\n\\n**5. Session Lifecycle:**\\n- Tests manually trigger agent sessions via `RunAgent()`\\n- Rewind points available before commit\\n- Commit triggers hook-based checkpoint creation\\n- Multiple sessions supported in same directory\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 11. Running E2E Tests\\n\\n**Command Line:**\\n```bash\\n# Default (claude-code agent)\\nE2E_AGENT=claude-code go test -tags=e2e ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# With specific model\\nE2E_CLAUDE_MODEL=opus E2E_AGENT=claude-code go test -tags=e2e ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# With timeout override\\nE2E_TIMEOUT=5m E2E_AGENT=claude-code go test -tags=e2e ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# Specific test\\nE2E_AGENT=claude-code go test -tags=e2e -run TestE2