er\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_0181CEqf7GRSQXhM1YhRyiu9\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive report on what I've discovered about the GitHub Copilot CLI integration and how to plan e2e testing for it.\\n\\n## Summary Report: GitHub Copilot CLI Agent Architecture & E2E Testing Requirements\\n\\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here's what I've discovered about how the GitHub Copilot CLI looks from the outside and how e2e tests should be structured:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. **Copilot CLI Binary Invocation**\\n\\n**Binary name**: `copilot` (command-line tool)\\n\\n**Resume command** (from `FormatResumeCommand` in copilot.go):\\n```go\\n// Line 227-229 in copilot.go\\nfunc (c *CopilotAgent) FormatResumeCommand(_ string) string {\\n    return \\\"copilot --resume\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSo to resume a session: `copilot --resume`\\n\\n**Other flags**: The codebase doesn't expose other CLI flags for Copilot yet, but based on the pattern with Claude Code and Gemini, the agent likely accepts:\\n- Prompts via stdin or `-p/--prompt` flag\\n- Tool restrictions via `--allowedTools` or similar\\n- Model selection (if multi-model)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. **Hook Configuration & Invocation Pattern**\\n\\nCopilot stores hooks in `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json` (not like Claude's `.claude/settings.json`):\\n\\n**Config structure** (from hooks.go and types in copilot.go):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [\\n      {\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"bash\\\": \\\"entire hooks github-copilot session-start\\\", \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10}\\n    ],\\n    \\\"agentStop\\\": [\\n      {\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"bash\\\": \\\"entire hooks github-copilot agent-stop\\\", \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10}\\n    ],\\n    ...\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Hook invocation pattern**:\\n```bash\\nentire hooks github-copilot <hook-subcommand>\\n```\\n\\nExample hook subcommands:\\n- `session-start`\\n- `session-end`\\n- `user-prompt-submitted`\\n- `agent-stop`\\n- `subagent-stop`\\n- `pre-tool-use`\\n- `post-tool-use`\\n- `error-occurred`\\n\\n**Hook stdin format** (from copilot.go ParseHookInput):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/events.jsonl\\\",\\n  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/working/directory\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"ISO8601\\\",\\n  \\\"hookEventName\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  // Hook-specific fields...\\n  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user prompt text\\\",  // for userPromptSubmitted\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"completion|cancelled\\\",  // for sessionEnd\\n  \\\"toolName\\\": \\\"string\\\",  // for pre/postToolUse\\n  \\\"toolArgs\\\": {...},\\n  \\\"toolResult\\\": {...}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. **Session Storage & Transcript Format**\\n\\n**Session directory**: `~/.copilot/session-state/` (overridable via `ENTIRE_TEST_COPILOT_SESSION_DIR` env var for testing)\\n\\n**Session file path**: `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n\\n**Transcript format**: JSONL (JSON Lines - one JSON object per line, like Claude Code)\\n\\n**Sample session structure**:\\n```\\n~/.copilot/session-state/\\n└── <sessionId>/\\n    └── events.jsonl      # JSONL transcript\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. **Agent Detection & Configuration**\\n\\nFrom `copilot.go` `DetectPresence()`:\\n\\n**Detection logic**:\\n1. Check if hooks are installed (`AreHooksInstalled()` → looks for `entire` commands in `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json`)\\n2. OR check for `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json` file existence\\n3. Returns `true` if either is detected\\n\\n**Agent name**: `\\\"github-copilot\\\"` (used in CLI: `--agent github-copilot` or `entire enable --agent github-copilot`)\\n\\n**Agent type**: `\\\"GitHub Copilot\\\"` (display name in metadata/trailers)\\n\\n**Preview status**: `IsPreview() = true` (marked as preview integration)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **Existing E2E Test Infrastructure P