   ✓ Project configured (.entire/settings.json)\\n   \\n   Ready.\\n   ```\\n\\n**Agent Detection** (auto-detection in interactive mode):\\n- Calls `agent.DetectAll()` which checks all registered agents' `DetectPresence()` methods\\n- Copilot detected if:\\n  - `.github/hooks/copilot-setup.json` with Entire hooks exists, OR\\n  - Hooks are already installed\\n\\n### 7. **Hook Dispatch Flow** (`cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go`)\\n\\n**Command Structure**:\\n```\\nentire hooks\\n├── git (strategy-level hooks)\\n└── github-copilot (agent-specific hooks)\\n    ├── session-start\\n    ├── session-end\\n    ├── user-prompt-submitted\\n    ├── agent-stop\\n    ├── subagent-stop\\n    ├── pre-tool-use\\n    ├── post-tool-use\\n    └── error-occurred\\n```\\n\\n**Hook Execution** (`newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging`):\\n1. **Early exits**:\\n   - Returns nil if not in a git repo\\n   - Returns nil if Entire is disabled\\n\\n2. **Logging context** set up with agent name\\n\\n3. **Hook parsing** via `agent.ParseHookEvent(hookName, stdin)`:\\n   - Copilot agent's `ParseHookEvent()` implementation in `lifecycle.go`\\n   - Reads and parses JSON from stdin\\n   - Returns normalized `Event` or `nil` (for pass-through hooks)\\n\\n4. **Event dispatch** (if event != nil):\\n   - Calls `DispatchLifecycleEvent(ag, event)`\\n   - Handles lifecycle state transitions and checkpoint creation\\n\\n5. **Special handling**:\\n   - PostTodo (Claude-specific) is handled separately\\n   - Other pass-through hooks (nil event) are no-ops\\n\\n6. **Logging** of duration and success\\n\\n### 8. **Hook Input Types** (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilot/types.go`)\\n\\nAll Copilot hooks include common base fields (JSON from stdin):\\n```go\\ntype hookBase struct {\\n    Timestamp int64  `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n    Cwd       string `json:\\\"cwd\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Hook-specific types**:\\n- `sessionStartRaw`: base + Source, InitialPrompt\\n- `sessionEndRaw`: base + Reason\\n- `userPromptRaw`: base + Prompt